orian" era="ce" normal="1843/1843">1843</unitdate><container id="aspace_ccc633141c143006f0c6bd6a1867ee8d" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_498e315578c8bbd76e76cae995ea40ad" parent="aspace_ccc633141c143006f0c6bd6a1867ee8d" type="folder">17</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_62940ac2599d23a370b4b8062e2b46d4" level="item"><did><unittitle>Tompkins County Election Returns, Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848 . Folder contains returns for various town, county, state, and federal elections held during this period. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>Ithaca Journal</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1836-11-30/1848-11-22" type="inclusive">Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848</unitdate><container id="aspace_03c1db50d1dec2b8b04ff063bbb07838" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_9fe4f50581db93dd01b879cc95638132" parent="aspace_03c1db50d1dec2b8b04ff063bbb07838" type="folder">18</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8a7f96942566fca8837cb11c0479e48f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Articles on slavery, abolition, and colonization, Apr. 5, 1837-Apr. 18, 1838. Folder contains assorted articles on the issues surrounding slavery. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>The Ithaca Journal and Herald</title>.</unittitle><container id="aspace_cf85524443895ef0d75aa90bcb354d41" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_d3b03ebef5e224b10691c1cef09098d8" parent="aspace_cf85524443895ef0d75aa90bcb354d41" type="folder">19</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_1c38f12fd9778ac3db661a741f138526" level="item"><did><unittitle>Residents of Tompkins County call meeting to discuss fiscal problems they believe caused by politicians in Albany. Article appears in May 7, 1834 <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1834-05-07/1834-05-